43 class ViscosityGuptaYos : public ViscosityAlgorithm, public GuptaYos
44 {
45 public:
46 
47  ViscosityGuptaYos(ViscosityAlgorithm::ARGS collisions)
48  : ViscosityAlgorithm(collisions),
49  A(collisions.nHeavy(), collisions.nHeavy()),
50  B(collisions.nHeavy(), collisions.nHeavy()),
51  a(collisions.nHeavy())
52  { }
53 
57  double viscosity()
58  {
59  const int ns = m_collisions.nSpecies();
60  const int nh = m_collisions.nHeavy();
61  const int k = ns - nh;
62 
63  const ArrayXd& nDij = m_collisions.nDij();
64  const ArrayXd& Ast = m_collisions.Astij();
65  const ArrayXd& mi = m_collisions.mass();
66  const Map<const ArrayXd> x(m_collisions.thermo().X()+k, nh);
67 
68  // Compute the symmetric matrix A and vector a
69  for (int j = 0, index = 0; j < nh; ++j) {
70  for (int i = j; i < nh; ++i, ++index) {
71  A(i,j) = (2.0-1.2*Ast(index))/((mi(i+k)+mi(j+k))*nDij(index));
72  B(i,j) = Ast(index) / nDij(index);
73  }
74  }
75 
76  // Leave B as symmetric and postpone dividing by m(i) until after B*x
77  // which uses fewer divides and allows for sym-matrix-vector product
78  a.matrix() = B.selfadjointView<Lower>() * x.matrix();
79  a *= 1.2 / mi.tail(nh);
80 
81  // Now compute the viscosity using Gupta-Yos
82  return guptaYos(A, a, x);
83  }
84 
85 private:
86 
87  ArrayXXd A;
88  MatrixXd B;
89  ArrayXd a;
90 };
